Get this itinerary for free if you follow me (DM Hi), else you can buy it through the link in bio. 

Here are a few things you should know about this Ladakh itinerary 👇

- It’s 36 pages of important information like, features 2 routes, maps, things to do, important traveller notes, stay options, estimated expenses, & of course pretty pictures! 
- Route #1 Delhi - Dobhi - Jispa - Gonbo Rangjon - Purne/Phuktal Monastery - Padum - 1 secret location - Sethan - Delhi
- Route #2 continues from Padum and explores the rest of Ladakh, Padum - Kargil - Leh - Korzok/Tso moriri - Hanle - Pangong tso - Nubra valley - Turtuk
- Information from the two routes is collected over me doing 2 trips which spanned over 38 days in that region. 
- Almost all locations have a video you can watch to learn more either on my handle or @tanyakhanijow ‘s Youtube. All links will are added to the guide. 
- I have added almost all the information I possibly could think of being important, including a list & links of essential things to carry.

- If you want this guide for free, follow me and DM, ill send it to you as soon as I can. (The itinerary is free for my followers, so its taking time for me to get through all the DMs).

- And if you would like to buy it off of me, no problem! The link is in bio, it costs Rs 99  for the first 2 days of this reel being live. After that it wi
ll be Rs 249

Background on me - I was working in a travel company for 5 years full time, before I started doing this, I consistently travel and like to share the gems I find with the people of my community. So if you plan to follow me, do it for that. 

I expect integrity and support from the people who want to join my community. And I promise to do my bit as well. 

The itinerary would not have been possible without the love and support of @tanyakhanijow ❤️

I’m purposely not tagging the host here, but he knows I’m grateful he hosted us so graciously. Thanks Punit bhai.

‼️Here’s all the information you’ll need 👇  

- This sport is for passionate motorsport & car enthusiasts and those who just love to drive.  

- The sport is more prevalent in southern India, so more courses will be happening in that region. 

- I did mine in Bengaluru, but sir is known to travel to different parts of the country to teach. 

- He is a renowned figure in the Indian Rally space, just google him.  @chetanshivram 

- The course is conducted over 2 days, and this is only Level 1 (there are 2 more levels, but they are more 1 on 1 in nature).

- But after level 1 you can compete in races, by just renting your gear and car. (sir will help you with his network, and yes you can rent from him too).

- He will also educated you about the different rally categories, and how you can even compete in some races even in your stock car! 

- The sport is expensive, and for some, the course will be on the higher side as well, but the amount of investment that the car needs to run and perform is so high, you will quickly understand why. 

- Reach out to sir, on his handle or his number to learn more about the course - 
+91 97412 40602

- People in and around Karnataka, can attend his next race event to see and experience everything first hand. I was going to compete in it, but unfortunately I am travelling on those dates. more details on his page.

Big hug to @tanyakhanijow for helping me shoot

And the great men of @revv_hard for the FPV footage

Here’s how you can compete is a race like this!

Rent a car and show up! 

- @chetanshivram sir, rents out his rally spec car to enthusiast at a minimal cost.

- You can reach the event on the day of and just directly compete.

- Location @gp1performancezone Chennammanapalya 

In your own car - 

- No matter what car you have, you will be placed in a category based on your engine power and modifications done to the car.

- Apart from that you will also be placed in either the Amateur or Professional category.

Any category participation will cost around 3500 
Car rental will also cost around the same keeping your entire budget under 7K

Plus you can compete in multiple categories on the day of the event and also do multiple laps to do your best.

It took me 4 laps to do my best numbers.

You get 2 laps as standard and 2 more upon additional payment.

Do this professionally

- If you’re looking to get into Autocross and rally races professionally then I would suggest you take up @chetanshivram sir’s rally course. 

- This will enable you to learn more about this sport and about all the races happening every week. 

Location of this race was @gp1performancezone 
Follow them for their upcoming races!

Here’s why Italy should be the next country you explore!

1. The best pizzas I have ever had, EVER. Napoli is the place to experiment and explore with Pizza. 

2. Wine is mindblowing. It just flows like water in Italy. 

3. Beaches might be crowded at some spots, but if you are polite and patient, you will find a good lounging area. Positano has the best-looking coast, but it’s quite expensive. 

4. Venice catches some flak for being touristy, but if you just decide to walk its streets all day, you will see how beautiful it is too. Sunsets are truly magical. 

5. Italians are loud and passionate, so you feel a lot more at home while walking the city streets. Also they love their football. 

6. DOLOMITES - The beautiful mountains of Italy deserve a 14 day itinerary on its own. The routes of treks and hikes are so well laid out, you don’t need any guide to explore the mountains. You can do it on your own!
